Uptime API

  • v3.1.0 (Production)
  • v3.0.0 (Production)
  • Documentation
  • SDKs (REST API Libraries)
  • Release Note

Overview

Welcome to the Uptime.com REST API!

To get started, login or signup and visit our API Token page or login to our navigatable API UI (Note our navigatable API and API Token access is only available to paid subscribers)

View our SDK

(Built with Restunited.com)

Base URL

All endpoints in the documentation starts with the following URL:

https://uptime.com

Authentication

No authentication required.

Installation Guide

  • ActionScript
  • Android
  • C#
  • Java
  • JavaScript
  • Objective-C
  • PHP
  • Python (v2)
  • Ruby
  • Scala

The ActionScript SDK (REST API library) is still under development. Please contact api@uptime.com if you would like pilot the beta version of the SDK.

Download and install
Please follow the instruction below to download the tarball, then build and install the SDK using Gradle

Copy
wget https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-java.tar.gz
tar mzxvf UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-java.tar.gz
cd UptimeApi-java
gradle install

Update build.gradle in your project

Copy
dependencies {
    compile 'com.uptime:uptime-api:3.1.0'
}

repositories {
    mavenLocal()
}

Import the packages

Copy
import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

import com.uptime.*;
import com.uptime.api.*;
import com.uptime.model.*;

Configure

Copy
ApiClient apiClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
// apiClient.setBasePath("https://uptime.com");

Download and Install
Please follow the instruction below to download the tarball and move the folder to the 'lib' folder in the project.

Copy
wget https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-csharp.tar.gz
tar mzxvf UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-csharp.tar.gz
mv UptimeApi-csharp /path/to/your/project/lib/

Add the library to the project in the IDE

  1. Open or create a C# application using your favorite IDE
  2. Add the folder UptimeApi-csharp to the project's "lib" folder
  3. Add System.Web, Microsoft.CSharp, System.Runtime.Serialization to the project's "References"
  4. Use NuGet to add RestSharp and Json.NET to the project (or manually add the DLLs under "bin" folder)

Import the following

Copy
using System;
using System.Web;
using System.IO;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using Com.Uptime.UptimeApi;
using Com.Uptime.UptimeApi.Api;
using Com.Uptime.UptimeApi.Model;
using Com.Uptime.UptimeApi.Client;

Download and install
Please follow the instruction below to download the tarball, then build and install the Java JAR using Maven

Copy
wget https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-java.tar.gz
tar mzxvf UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-java.tar.gz
cd UptimeApi-java
mvn install

Update pom.xml

Copy
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.uptime</groupId>
    <artifactId>uptime-api</artifactId>
    <version>3.1.0</version>
    <scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>

Import the packages

Copy
import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

import com.uptime.*;
import com.uptime.api.*;
import com.uptime.model.*;

Configure

Copy
ApiClient apiClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
// apiClient.setBasePath("https://uptime.com");

Use with Node.js
Please follow the instructions below to use the SDK with Node.js

Install swagger-client, if needed:

Copy
npm install swagger-client

Then setup the API client:

Copy
var fs = require('fs');
var client = require("swagger-client");

var swagger = new client({
  url: 'https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/swagger2/swagger.json',
  success: function() {
    // the API client "swagger" is ready here
  }
});

Use with browser

Include swagger-client.min.js in the HTML page:

Copy
<script src="http://files1.restunited.com/swagger-js/swagger-client.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>

Then setup the API client:

Copy
window.swagger = new SwaggerClient({
  url: 'https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/swagger2/swagger.json',
  success: function() {
    // the API client "swagger" is ready here
  }
});

The Objective-C SDK (REST API library) is still under development. Please contact api@uptime.com if you would like pilot the beta version of the SDK.

Download and install
Please follow the instruction below to download the tarball in your project folder and then install the PHP libraries

Copy
wget https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-php.tar.gz
tar mzxvf UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-php.tar.gz

(Optional) If php5-curl package not yet installed, please run

Copy
sudo apt-get install php5-curl

Import the library

Copy
<?php
require_once 'UptimeApi-php/autoload.php';

// uncomment below to set timezone ref: http://php.net/manual/en/timezones.php
//date_default_timezone_set('America/New_York');

// uncomment below to enable debugging
// UptimeApi-php\Configuration::getDefaultConfiguration()->setDebug(TRUE);


?>

Download and install
Please follow the instruction below to download the tarball and then install the Python modules

Copy
wget https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-python.tar.gz
tar mzxvf UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-python.tar.gz
cd UptimeApi-python
python setup.py install --user

(Optional) To install the module for all users, please run

Copy
sudo python setup.py install

Import the Python modules

Copy
import time
import uptime_api
from uptime_api.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

Download and Install
Please follow the instruction below to download and use the Ruby SDK

Copy
wget https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-ruby.tar.gz
tar mzxvf UptimeApi-prod-3.1.0-ruby.tar.gz

To use the SDK without installing it as a gem, run with the -I flag as follows:

Copy
ruby -IUptimeApi-ruby/lib your-ruby-file.rb

Otherwise build the SDK into a Ruby gem and install it locally:

Copy
cd UptimeApi-ruby
gem build uptime_api.gemspec
gem install ./uptime_api-3.1.0.gem

To use the Ruby gem with Bundler, include the following in Gemfile and run bundle install

Copy
gem "uptime_api", "~> 3.1.0"

Require the Ruby gem

Copy
require 'uptime_api'

(Optional) Configuration
Initialize configuration with other values

Copy
UptimeApi.configure do |config|
  config.scheme = 'https'
  config.host = 'uptime.com'
  config.base_path = ''
  config.inject_format = false
end

The Scala SDK (REST API library) is still under development. Please contact api@uptime.com if you would like pilot the beta version of the SDK.

Testing
To faciliate testing, the following example code contains all the endpoint methods available in the SDK.

  • ActionScript
  • Android
  • C#
  • Java
  • JavaScript
  • Objective-C
  • PHP
  • Python (v2)
  • Ruby
  • Scala
Example Code in ActionScript is being worked on at the moment.
Copy
// File: UptimeApi-java/src/main/java/com/uptime/UptimeApiTestAndroid.java

package com.uptime;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

import com.uptime.*;
import com.uptime.api.*;
import com.uptime.model.*;

public class UptimeApiTestAndroid {
    private ApiClient apiClient;

    public UptimeApiTestAndroid() {
        apiClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // apiClient.setBasePath("https://uptime.com");
    }

    public void testChecksAddBlacklistWeb() {
        String mspAddress = "sampleMspAddress";  // Domain (Please enter either the domain (example - ...
        String name = "sampleName";  // name
        String mspExpectString = "sampleMspExpectString";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspDnsServer = "sampleMspDnsServer";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspSendString = "sampleMspSendString";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspPassword = "sampleMspPassword";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspEncryption = "sampleMspEncryption";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspDnsRecordType = "sampleMspDnsRecordType";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspUsername = "sampleMspUsername";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspInterval = "sampleMspInterval";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspThreshold = "sampleMspThreshold";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspPort = "sampleMspPort";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspUrlPath = "sampleMspUrlPath";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        String mspUrlScheme = "sampleMspUrlScheme";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check

        try {
            WebApi webApi = new WebApi();
            CheckChangeRecordSerializer response = webApi.checksAddBlacklist(mspAddress, name, mspExpectString, mspDnsServer, mspSendString, mspPassword, mspEncryption, mspDnsRecordType, mspUsername, mspInterval, mspThreshold, mspPort, mspUrlPath, mspUrlScheme);
            System.out.println(response);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.out.printf("ApiException caught: %s\n", e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    public void testUserCreateWeb() {
        String firstName = "sampleFirstName";  // First Name
        String lastName = "sampleLastName";  // Last Name
        String email = "sampleEmail";  // Email Address
        String password = "samplePassword";  // Password
        Boolean notifyUptimeReport = false;  // Notify Weekly Uptime Report

        try {
            WebApi webApi = new WebApi();
            UserChangeRecordSerializer response = webApi.userCreate(firstName, lastName, email, password, notifyUptimeReport);
            System.out.println(response);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.out.printf("ApiException caught: %s\n", e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    public void testPushNotificationCreateWeb() {
        String alias = "sampleAlias";  // alias
        String hipchatRoom = "sampleHipchatRoom";  // hipchat_room
        String hipchatServer = "sampleHipchatServer";  // hipchat_server
        String hipchatToken = "sampleHipchatToken";  // hipchat_token
        Boolean pagerdutyAutoresolve = false;  // pagerduty_autoresolve
        String pagerdutyKey = "samplePagerdutyKey";  // pagerduty_key
        String postbackUrl = "samplePostbackUrl";  // postback_url
        String pushbulletEmail = "samplePushbulletEmail";  // pushbullet_email
        String pushoverKey = "samplePushoverKey";  // pushover_key
        String slackRoom = "sampleSlackRoom";  // slack_room
        String slackWebhookUrl = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl";  // slack_webhook_url
        String tweetHandle = "sampleTweetHandle";  // tweet_handle
        String victorOpsApiKey = "sampleVictorOpsApiKey";  // victor_ops_api_key
        String victorOpsCustomRoutingKey = "sampleVictorOpsCustomRoutingKey";  // victor_ops_custom_routing_key
        Boolean victorOpsRoutingKeyType = false;  // victor_ops_routing_key_type
        String cOPYFROMupdateandmakeallrequired = "sampleCopyfromupdateandmakeallrequired";  // COPYFROMupdateandmakeallrequired

        try {
            WebApi webApi = new WebApi();
            PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer response = webApi.pushNotificationCreate(alias, hipchatRoom, hipchatServer, hipchatToken, pagerdutyAutoresolve, pagerdutyKey, postbackUrl, pushbulletEmail, pushoverKey, slackRoom, slackWebhookUrl, tweetHandle, victorOpsApiKey, victorOpsCustomRoutingKey, victorOpsRoutingKeyType, cOPYFROMupdateandmakeallrequired);
            System.out.println(response);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.out.printf("ApiException caught: %s\n", e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    public void testChecksAddDnsWeb() {
        String mspExpectString = "sampleMspExpectString";  // String to expect (IP Address, Domain Name or String to...
        String mspDnsServer = "sampleMspDnsServer";  // DNS server (Please enter the DNS server(example - ...
        String mspDnsRecordType = "sampleMspDnsRecordType";  // Record type (Select the type of DNS record you would like...
        String mspInterval = "sampleMspInterval";  // Check interval (The interval in which to make the network...
        String mspAddress = "sampleMspAddress";  // Domain or IP (Please enter the domain (example - ...
        String name = "sampleName";  // name
        String mspSendString = "sampleMspSendString";  // Field not applicable for a DNS check
        String mspPassword = "sampleMspPassword";  // Field not applicable for a DNS check

        String mspThreshold = "sampleMspThreshold";  // Field not applicable for a DNS check
        String mspPort = "sampleMspPort";  // Field not applicable for a DNS check
        String mspUrlPath = "sampleMspUrlPath";  // Field not applicable for a DNS check
        String mspUrlScheme = "sampleMspUrlScheme";  // Field not applicable for a DNS check

        try {
            WebApi webApi = new WebApi();
            CheckChangeRecordSerializer response = webApi.checksAddDns(mspExpectString, mspDnsServer, mspDnsRecordType, mspInterval, mspAddress, name, mspSendString, mspPassword, mspEncryption, mspUsername, mspThreshold, mspPort, mspUrlPath, mspUrlScheme);

        String mspUsername = "sampleMspUsername";  // Search for usernames to connect to

    public void sleep(int milliseconds) {
        try {
            Thread.sleep(milliseconds);
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            throw new RuntimeException(e);
        }
    }

    public void sleep(int milliseconds) {
        try {
            Thread.sleep(milliseconds);
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            throw new RuntimeException(e);
        }
    }

// Run this file:
//   cd UptimeApi-java
//   mvn compile exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.uptime.UptimeApiTestJava"

// File: main.js

var fs = require('fs');
var client = require("swagger-client");

function testChecksAddBlacklistWeb() {
  var args = {};
  args['msp_address'] = "sampleMspAddress"; // Domain (Please enter either the domain (example - ...
  args['name'] = "sampleName"; // name
  args['msp_expect_string'] = "sampleMspExpectString"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_dns_server'] = "sampleMspDnsServer"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_send_string'] = "sampleMspSendString"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_password'] = "sampleMspPassword"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_encryption'] = "sampleMspEncryption"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_dns_record_type'] = "sampleMspDnsRecordType"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_username'] = "sampleMspUsername"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_interval'] = "sampleMspInterval"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_threshold'] = "sampleMspThreshold"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
  args['msp_port'] = "sampleMspPort"; // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check

  url: 'https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/files1.restunited.com/libraries/uptime_api_20150821140100/prod/3/1/0/sw/swagger2/swagger.json',
  success: function() {
    // run all tests
    main();
  }
});

class UptimeApiTest {
    function testChecksAddBlacklistWeb() {
        // initialize the API client with default base URL: https://uptime.com
        $api_client = new UptimeApi\ApiClient();

        $mspAddress = "sampleMspAddress";  // Domain (Please enter either the domain (example - ...
        $name = "sampleName";  // name
        $mspExpectString = "sampleMspExpectString";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspDnsServer = "sampleMspDnsServer";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspSendString = "sampleMspSendString";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspPassword = "sampleMspPassword";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspEncryption = "sampleMspEncryption";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspDnsRecordType = "sampleMspDnsRecordType";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspUsername = "sampleMspUsername";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspInterval = "sampleMspInterval";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspThreshold = "sampleMspThreshold";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspPort = "sampleMspPort";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspUrlPath = "sampleMspUrlPath";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check
        $mspUrlScheme = "sampleMspUrlScheme";  // Field not applicable for a BLACKLIST check

        try {
            $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
            // return <a href="#model_CheckChangeRecordSerializer">CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)</a>
            $response = $web_api->checksAddBlacklist($mspAddress, $name, $mspExpectString, $mspDnsServer, $mspSendString, $mspPassword, $mspEncryption, $mspDnsRecordType, $mspUsername, $mspInterval, $mspThreshold, $mspPort, $mspUrlPath, $mspUrlScheme);
            print_r($response);
        } catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
            echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
            echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
            echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
        }
    }

        echo 'Calling endpoint: pushNotificationDestroy ... ';
        $this->testPushNotificationDestroyWeb();

# File: uptime_api_test.rb

require 'uptime_api'

UptimeApi.configure do |config|
  config.scheme = 'https'
  config.host = 'uptime.com'
  config.base_path = ''
  config.inject_format = false
end

class UptimeApiTest
  def test_checks_add_blacklist_web
    msp_address = "sample_msp_address"  # Domain (Please enter either the domain (example - ...

    begin
      web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
      # return <a href="#model_CheckChangeRecordSerializer">CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)</a>
      response = web_api.checks_add_blacklist(msp_address, :name => "sample_name", :msp_expect_string => "sample_msp_expect_string", :msp_dns_server => "sample_msp_dns_server", :msp_send_string => "sample_msp_send_string", :msp_password => "sample_msp_password", :msp_encryption => "sample_msp_encryption", :msp_dns_record_type => "sample_msp_dns_record_type", :msp_username => "sample_msp_username", :msp_interval => "sample_msp_interval", :msp_threshold => "sample_msp_threshold", :msp_port => "sample_msp_port", :msp_url_path => "sample_msp_url_path", :msp_url_scheme => "sample_msp_url_scheme")
      p response
    rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
      puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
      puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
      puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
      puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"
    end
  end

A JSON object with a key of "contact_ids" containing a list of contact group IDs to add to existing id's. Example {"contact_ids":[1,2,3,4]} To add contact groups 1,2,3 and 4 in a particular Check

checksAddDns
Add a new DNS check

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/add-dns/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new DNS check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

String to expect (IP Address, Domain Name or String to expect in response.)

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

DNS server (Please enter the DNS server(example - ns1.registrar.com))

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

Record type (Select the type of DNS record you would like to test for.)

msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

Check interval (The interval in which to make the network request)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

Domain or IP (Please enter the domain (example - www.google.com), or the IP for reverse DNS checks.)

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

msp_passwordStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

msp_portStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a DNS check

This endpoint returns CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)


Error CodeMessage
400PARSE_ERROR
401NOT_AUTHORIZED
403PERMISSION_DENIED
404NOT_FOUND
500UNKNOWN

checksAddHttp
Add a new HTTP check

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/add-http/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new HTTP check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

Check interval (The interval in which to make the network request)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

URL (Please enter either the domain (example - www.google.com) or the IP address(example - 1.1.1.1).)

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Scheme

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

String to expect (A text string to expect in the html content of the page. If the text is not present the check will fail.)

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a HTTP check

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

String to POST (URL encoded http POST data that will be posted to the page, for example submitting a login form with a username and password.)

msp_passwordStringHTTP Form

Password (The password required (Basic HTTP Authentication), if any.)

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a HTTP check

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a HTTP check

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Username (The username required (Basic HTTP Authentication), if any.)

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a HTTP check

msp_portStringHTTP Form

Port

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Path (The path of the request)

This endpoint returns CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)


Error CodeMessage
400PARSE_ERROR
401NOT_AUTHORIZED
403PERMISSION_DENIED
404NOT_FOUND
500UNKNOWN

Request preview:

$mspInterval = "sampleMspInterval";  // Check interval (The interval in which to make the network...
$mspAddress = "sampleMspAddress";  // URL (Please enter either the domain (example - ...
$mspUrlScheme = "sampleMspUrlScheme";  // Scheme
$name = "sampleName";  // name
$mspExpectString = "sampleMspExpectString";  // String to expect (A text string to expect in the html...
$mspDnsServer = "sampleMspDnsServer";  // Field not applicable for a HTTP check
$mspSendString = "sampleMspSendString";  // String to POST (URL encoded http POST data that will be...
$mspPassword = "sampleMspPassword";  // Password (The password required (Basic HTTP...
$mspEncryption = "sampleMspEncryption";  // Field not applicable for a HTTP check
$mspDnsRecordType = "sampleMspDnsRecordType";  // Field not applicable for a HTTP check
$mspUsername = "sampleMspUsername";  // Username (The username required (Basic HTTP...
$mspThreshold = "sampleMspThreshold";  // Field not applicable for a HTTP check
$mspPort = "sampleMspPort";  // Port
$mspUrlPath = "sampleMspUrlPath";  // Path (The path of the request)

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->checksAddHttp($mspInterval, $mspAddress, $mspUrlScheme, $name, $mspExpectString, $mspDnsServer, $mspSendString, $mspPassword, $mspEncryption, $mspDnsRecordType, $mspUsername, $mspThreshold, $mspPort, $mspUrlPath);

    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
}

msp_interval = "sample_msp_interval"  # Check interval (The interval in which to make the network...
msp_address = "sample_msp_address"  # URL (Please enter either the domain (example - ...
msp_url_scheme = "sample_msp_url_scheme"  # Scheme

begin
  web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
  # return CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.checks_add_http(msp_interval, msp_address, msp_url_scheme, :name => "sample_name", :msp_expect_string => "sample_msp_expect_string", :msp_dns_server => "sample_msp_dns_server", :msp_send_string => "sample_msp_send_string", :msp_password => "sample_msp_password", :msp_encryption => "sample_msp_encryption", :msp_dns_record_type => "sample_msp_dns_record_type", :msp_username => "sample_msp_username", :msp_threshold => "sample_msp_threshold", :msp_port => "sample_msp_port", :msp_url_path => "sample_msp_url_path")
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
  puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"
end

checksAddIcmp
Add a new ICMP check

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/add-icmp/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new ICMP check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

Check interval (The interval in which to make the network request)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

Domain or IP (Please enter either the domain(example - www.google.com) or the IP address(example - 8.8.8.8).)

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_passwordStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_portStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a ICMP check

This endpoint returns CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)


Error CodeMessage
400PARSE_ERROR
401NOT_AUTHORIZED
403PERMISSION_DENIED
404NOT_FOUND
500UNKNOWN

checksAddImap
Add a new IMAP check

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/add-imap/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new IMAP check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

Check interval (The interval in which to make the network request)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

Domain or IP (Please enter either the domain(example - www.google.com) or the IP address(example - 1.1.1.1).)

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

String to expect (The string to expect back. Default is "OK".)

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

msp_passwordStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Encryption (Use SSL for the connection.)

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

msp_portStringHTTP Form

Port (Port number you would like to use (default - 143).)

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a IMAP check

This endpoint returns CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)

checksAddSmtp
Add a new SMTP check

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/add-smtp/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new SMTP check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

Check interval (The interval in which to make the network request)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

Domain or IP (Please enter either the domain(example - www.google.com) or the IP address(example - 1.1.1.1).)

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

String to expect (String to expect in server response (may be repeated).)

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a SMTP check

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a SMTP check

msp_passwordStringHTTP Form

Password (The password for the username, if any.)

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Encryption (Use STARTTLS for the connection.)

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a SMTP check

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Username (The username required for the SMTP server, if any.)

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a SMTP check

msp_portStringHTTP Form

Port (Port number you would like to use (default - 25).)

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a SMTP check

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a SMTP check

This endpoint returns CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)


Error CodeMessage
400PARSE_ERROR
401NOT_AUTHORIZED
403PERMISSION_DENIED
404NOT_FOUND
500UNKNOWN

// initialize the API client with default base URL: https://uptime.com
$api_client = new UptimeApi\ApiClient();

$mspInterval = "sampleMspInterval";  // Check interval (The interval in which to make the network...
$mspAddress = "sampleMspAddress";  // Domain or IP (Please enter either the hostname(example - ...
$name = "sampleName";  // name
$mspExpectString = "sampleMspExpectString";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspDnsServer = "sampleMspDnsServer";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspSendString = "sampleMspSendString";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspPassword = "sampleMspPassword";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspEncryption = "sampleMspEncryption";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspDnsRecordType = "sampleMspDnsRecordType";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspUsername = "sampleMspUsername";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspThreshold = "sampleMspThreshold";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspPort = "sampleMspPort";  // Port (Port number you would like to use (default -  22))
$mspUrlPath = "sampleMspUrlPath";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check
$mspUrlScheme = "sampleMspUrlScheme";  // Field not applicable for a SSH check

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->checksAddSsh($mspInterval, $mspAddress, $name, $mspExpectString, $mspDnsServer, $mspSendString, $mspPassword, $mspEncryption, $mspDnsRecordType, $mspUsername, $mspThreshold, $mspPort, $mspUrlPath, $mspUrlScheme);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
}

msp_interval = "sample_msp_interval"  # Check interval (The interval in which to make the network...
msp_address = "sample_msp_address"  # Domain or IP (Please enter either the hostname(example - ...

begin
  web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
  # return CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.checks_add_ssh(msp_interval, msp_address, :name => "sample_name", :msp_expect_string => "sample_msp_expect_string", :msp_dns_server => "sample_msp_dns_server", :msp_send_string => "sample_msp_send_string", :msp_password => "sample_msp_password", :msp_encryption => "sample_msp_encryption", :msp_dns_record_type => "sample_msp_dns_record_type", :msp_username => "sample_msp_username", :msp_threshold => "sample_msp_threshold", :msp_port => "sample_msp_port", :msp_url_path => "sample_msp_url_path", :msp_url_scheme => "sample_msp_url_scheme")
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
  puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"
end

checksAddTcp
Add a new TCP check

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/add-tcp/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new TCP check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

Check interval (The interval in which to make the network request)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

Domain or IP (Please enter either the domain(example - www.google.com) or the IP address(example - 1.1.1.1).)

msp_portStringHTTP Form

Port (TCP Port number you would like to check.)

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

String to expect (String to expect in server response (may be repeated).)

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

String to send (String to send to the server)

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

msp_passwordStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a TCP check

This endpoint returns CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)


Error CodeMessage
400PARSE_ERROR
401NOT_AUTHORIZED
403PERMISSION_DENIED
404NOT_FOUND
500UNKNOWN

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new UDP check


  • Parameter

  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

String to expect (String to expect in server response (may be repeated).)

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

String to send (String to send to the server.)

msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

Check interval (The interval in which to make the network request)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

Domain or IP (Please enter either the domain(example - www.google.com) or the IP address(example - 1.1.1.1).)

msp_portStringHTTP Form

Port (The port you wish to use.)

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a UDP check

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a UDP check

Field not applicable for a UDP check

Field not applicable for a UDP check

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a UDP check

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a UDP check

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a UDP check

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Field not applicable for a UDP check

checksAddWhois

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/add-whois/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Add a new WHOIS check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

Whois info (The current domain registration info that should always match.)

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

Domain (Please enter the domain (example - www.google.com).)

msp_thresholdStringHTTP Form

Before expiry (Raise an alert if there are less than this many days before the domain needs to be renewed.)

nameStringHTTP Form

name

Field not applicable for a WHOIS check

$mspThreshold = "sampleMspThreshold";  // Before expiry (Raise an alert if there are less than this...
$name = "sampleName";  // name
$mspDnsServer = "sampleMspDnsServer";  // Field not applicable for a WHOIS check

$mspDnsRecordType = "sampleMspDnsRecordType";  // Field not applicable for a WHOIS check
$mspUsername = "sampleMspUsername";  // Field not applicable for a WHOIS check
$mspInterval = "sampleMspInterval";  // Field not applicable for a WHOIS check
$mspPort = "sampleMspPort";  // Field not applicable for a WHOIS check

    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->checksAddWhois($mspExpectString, $mspAddress, $mspThreshold, $name, $mspDnsServer, $mspSendString, $mspPassword, $mspEncryption, $mspDnsRecordType, $mspUsername, $mspInterval, $mspPort, $mspUrlPath, $mspUrlScheme);

  # return CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.checks_add_whois(msp_expect_string, msp_address, msp_threshold, :name => "sample_name", :msp_dns_server => "sample_msp_dns_server", :msp_send_string => "sample_msp_send_string", :msp_password => "sample_msp_password", :msp_encryption => "sample_msp_encryption", :msp_dns_record_type => "sample_msp_dns_record_type", :msp_username => "sample_msp_username", :msp_interval => "sample_msp_interval", :msp_port => "sample_msp_port", :msp_url_path => "sample_msp_url_path", :msp_url_scheme => "sample_msp_url_scheme")
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"

  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"

checksList
List all Checks

GET https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks List all Checks


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
pageStringHTTP Form

Paginate the resultset

orderingStringHTTP Form

Order the resultset by any field using the field name key of you see in the results

monitoring_service_typeStringHTTP Form

Search by check type (HTTP, ICMP, SSH, TCP, UDP, DNS, SMTP, POP, IMAP, BLACKLIST)

device__addressStringHTTP Form

Search by server hostname or address

device__idStringHTTP Form

Search by server primary key

contact_groups__nameStringHTTP Form

Search by contact group name

contact_groups__idStringHTTP Form

Search by contact group primary key

is_pausedBooleanHTTP Form

Search by paused (True/False)

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

Search by DNS Record Types (ANY, A, AAAA, CNAME, MX, NS, PTR, SOA, TXT)

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

Search by DNS Server

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

Search "SSL_TLS" to find SMTP servers with SSL enabled

msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

Search for expect strings

msp_url_pathStringHTTP Form

Search for servers with common checks with same URLs

msp_url_schemeStringHTTP Form

Search for "HTTP" or "HTTPS"

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

Search for usernames to connect to

nameStringHTTP Form

Search for check name or alias

This endpoint returns CheckPaginationSerializer (model)


Error CodeMessage
400PARSE_ERROR
401NOT_AUTHORIZED
403PERMISSION_DENIED
500UNKNOWN

Request preview:

Copy
GET /api/v1/monitoring-checks/ HTTP/1.1
Host: uptime.com
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

contact_groups__id=CONTACT_GROUPS__ID&contact_groups__name=CONTACT_GROUPS__NAME&device__address=DEVICE__ADDRESS&device__id=DEVICE__ID&is_paused=IS_PAUSED&monitoring_service_type=MONITORING_SERVICE_TYPE&msp_dns_record_type=MSP_DNS_RECORD_TYPE&msp_dns_server=MSP_DNS_SERVER&msp_encryption=MSP_ENCRYPTION&msp_expect_string=MSP_EXPECT_STRING&msp_url_path=MSP_URL_PATH&msp_url_scheme=MSP_URL_SCHEME&msp_username=MSP_USERNAME&name=NAME&ordering=ORDERING&page=PAGE

// initialize the API client with default base URL: https://uptime.com
$api_client = new UptimeApi\ApiClient();

$pk = "samplePk";  // pk
$name = "sampleName";  // Check Name
$mspExpectString = "sampleMspExpectString";  // String to expect
$mspDnsServer = "sampleMspDnsServer";  // DNS Server (Only for Type DNS)
$mspSendString = "sampleMspSendString";  // String to send
$mspPassword = "sampleMspPassword";  // Password to connect to host
$mspEncryption = "sampleMspEncryption";  // Use STARTTLS for the connection (Only for Type SMTP/POP)
$mspDnsRecordType = "sampleMspDnsRecordType";  // DNS Record type (Only for Type DNS)
$mspUsername = "sampleMspUsername";  // Username to connect to host
$mspInterval = "sampleMspInterval";  // msp_interval
$mspAddress = "sampleMspAddress";  // Domain or IP address or URL
$mspThreshold = 56;  // msp_threshold
$mspPort = "sampleMspPort";  // Port

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->checksPartialUpdate($pk, $name, $mspExpectString, $mspDnsServer, $mspSendString, $mspPassword, $mspEncryption, $mspDnsRecordType, $mspUsername, $mspInterval, $mspAddress, $mspThreshold, $mspPort);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
}

  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"

checksReplaceMonitoringGroups
Replace Locations For A Check

PATCH https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/:pk/replace-locations/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Replace Locations For A Check


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
pkStringPart of URL

pk

nameStringHTTP Form

name

msp_expect_stringStringHTTP Form

msp_expect_string

msp_dns_serverStringHTTP Form

msp_dns_server

msp_send_stringStringHTTP Form

msp_send_string

msp_passwordStringHTTP Form

msp_password

msp_encryptionStringHTTP Form

msp_encryption

Enumerated Values: , SSL_TLS

msp_dns_record_typeStringHTTP Form

msp_dns_record_type

Enumerated Values: ANY, A, AAAA, CNAME, MX, NS, PTR, SOA, TXT

msp_usernameStringHTTP Form

msp_username

msp_intervalStringHTTP Form

msp_interval

msp_addressStringHTTP Form

msp_address

msp_thresholdInteger (signed 32 bits)HTTP Form

msp_threshold

msp_portInteger (signed 32 bits)HTTP Form

msp_port

required_valuesStringHTTP Form

A JSON object with a key of "location_names" containing a list of IDs to replace existing id's. Example {"location_names":["USA", "DEU"]}

This endpoint returns CheckChangeRecordSerializer (model)

checksRetrieve
Get a Single Check

GET https://uptime.com/api/v1/monitoring-checks/:pk/

This endpoint helps you manage your Checks Get a Single CheckNote that the fields returned will vary based on the type of check that the record is. It will only show fields that are visible in the add_* POST methods and POST documentation. Whereas on the GET request listing all records, this shows all fields on the table exposed in the API and some fields might be blank even though the fields will be ignored for that type of check.

}

    api_client = uptime_api.ApiClient()
    web_api = uptime_api.WebApi(apiclient)

    # return ContactGroupChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    response = web_api.contact_group_update(pk, name, email_list, sms_list="sample_sms_list", push_notifications="sample_push_notifications")    

    pprint(response)


    # asynchronous call
    # thread = web_api.contact_group_update(pk, name, email_list, sms_list="sample_sms_list", push_notifications="sample_push_notifications", callback=callback_function)

except ApiException as e:
    print(e)

begin
  web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
  # return ContactGroupChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.contact_group_update(pk, name, email_list, :sms_list => "sample_sms_list", :push_notifications => "sample_push_notifications")
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
  puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"

$ordering = "sampleOrdering";  // Order the resultset by any field using the field name key...
$address = "sampleAddress";  // Search by server address
$name = "sampleName";  // Search by server name/alias
$isPaused = False;  // Search by whether an entire server is paused or not...

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return ServerPaginationSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->deviceList($page, $ordering, $address, $name, $isPaused);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";

    # (optional) initialize the API client with default base URL: http://petstore.swagger.io/v2

    # return ServerPaginationSerializer (model)

List all Incidents

This endpoint helps you manage your Incidents List all Incidents


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
pageStringHTTP Form

Paginate the resultset

orderingStringHTTP Form

Order the resultset by any field using the field name key of you see in the results

state_has_changedBooleanHTTP Form

State has Changed (True/False)

state_is_upBooleanHTTP Form

Server is Up (True/False)

device__addressStringHTTP Form

Server or IP Address

alert__outputStringHTTP Form

Raw output from Alert

alert__stateStringHTTP Form

State of Server (OK, WARNING, CRITICAL, UNKNOWN, UP, DOWN, UNREACHABLE)

alert__typeStringHTTP Form

Alert Type (SOFT, HARD)

This endpoint returns IncidentsPaginationSerializer (model)

500UNKNOWN

$stateHasChanged = False;  // State has Changed (True/False)
$stateIsUp = False;  // Server is Up (True/False)
$deviceAddress = "sampleDeviceAddress";  // Server or IP Address
$alertOutput = "sampleAlertOutput";  // Raw output from Alert
$alertState = "sampleAlertState";  // State of Server (OK, WARNING, CRITICAL, UNKNOWN, UP,...
$alertType = "sampleAlertType";  // Alert Type (SOFT, HARD)

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return IncidentsPaginationSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->incidentsList($page, $ordering, $stateHasChanged, $stateIsUp, $deviceAddress, $alertOutput, $alertState, $alertType);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";

except ApiException as e:
    print(e)

  p response

String pagerdutyKey = "samplePagerdutyKey";  // pagerduty_key
String pushbulletEmail = "samplePushbulletEmail";  // pushbullet_email
String pushoverKey = "samplePushoverKey";  // pushover_key

String slackWebhookUrl = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl";  // slack_webhook_url

    WebApi webApi = new WebApi();

String hipchatToken = "sampleHipchatToken";  // Hipchat Token
String alias = "sampleAlias";  // Alias
String hipchatRoom = "sampleHipchatRoom";  // Hipchat Room
String hipchatServer = "sampleHipchatServer";  // Hipchat Server
Boolean pagerdutyAutoresolve = false;  // pagerduty_autoresolve
String pagerdutyKey = "samplePagerdutyKey";  // pagerduty_key
String postbackUrl = "samplePostbackUrl";  // postback_url
String pushbulletEmail = "samplePushbulletEmail";  // pushbullet_email
String pushoverKey = "samplePushoverKey";  // pushover_key
String slackRoom = "sampleSlackRoom";  // slack_room
String slackWebhookUrl = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl";  // slack_webhook_url
String tweetHandle = "sampleTweetHandle";  // tweet_handle
String victorOpsApiKey = "sampleVictorOpsApiKey";  // victor_ops_api_key
String victorOpsCustomRoutingKey = "sampleVictorOpsCustomRoutingKey";  // victor_ops_custom_routing_key
Boolean victorOpsRoutingKeyType = false;  // victor_ops_routing_key_type

try {
    WebApi webApi = new WebApi();
    PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer response = webApi.pushNotificationAddHipChat(hipchatToken, alias, hipchatRoom, hipchatServer, pagerdutyAutoresolve, pagerdutyKey, postbackUrl, pushbulletEmail, pushoverKey, slackRoom, slackWebhookUrl, tweetHandle, victorOpsApiKey, victorOpsCustomRoutingKey, victorOpsRoutingKeyType);
    System.out.println(response);
} catch (ApiException e) {
    System.out.printf("ApiException caught: %s\n", e.getMessage());
}

curl -X POST --include "https://uptime.com/api/v1/alerting-push-notifications/add_hip_chat/" \
  -d "hipchat_token=<hipchat_token>" \
  -d "alias=<alias>" \
  -d "hipchat_room=<hipchat_room>" \
  -d "hipchat_server=<hipchat_server>" \
  -d "pagerduty_autoresolve=<pagerduty_autoresolve>" \
  -d "pagerduty_key=<pagerduty_key>" \
  -d "postback_url=<postback_url>" \
  -d "pushbullet_email=<pushbullet_email>" \
  -d "pushover_key=<pushover_key>" \
  -d "slack_room=<slack_room>" \
  -d "slack_webhook_url=<slack_webhook_url>" \
  -d "tweet_handle=<tweet_handle>" \
  -d "victor_ops_api_key=<victor_ops_api_key>" \
  -d "victor_ops_custom_routing_key=<victor_ops_custom_routing_key>" \
  -d "victor_ops_routing_key_type=<victor_ops_routing_key_type>"

String hipchatToken = "sampleHipchatToken";  // Hipchat Token
String alias = "sampleAlias";  // Alias
String hipchatRoom = "sampleHipchatRoom";  // Hipchat Room
String hipchatServer = "sampleHipchatServer";  // Hipchat Server
bool? pagerdutyAutoresolve = false;  // pagerduty_autoresolve
String pagerdutyKey = "samplePagerdutyKey";  // pagerduty_key
String postbackUrl = "samplePostbackUrl";  // postback_url
String pushbulletEmail = "samplePushbulletEmail";  // pushbullet_email
String pushoverKey = "samplePushoverKey";  // pushover_key
String slackRoom = "sampleSlackRoom";  // slack_room
String slackWebhookUrl = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl";  // slack_webhook_url
String tweetHandle = "sampleTweetHandle";  // tweet_handle
String victorOpsApiKey = "sampleVictorOpsApiKey";  // victor_ops_api_key
String victorOpsCustomRoutingKey = "sampleVictorOpsCustomRoutingKey";  // victor_ops_custom_routing_key
bool? victorOpsRoutingKeyType = false;  // victor_ops_routing_key_type

try
{
    // first arguemnt 'basePath' is optional
    WebApi webApi = new WebApi("https://uptime.com");
    PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer response = webApi.PushNotificationAddHipChat(hipchatToken, alias, hipchatRoom, hipchatServer, pagerdutyAutoresolve, pagerdutyKey, postbackUrl, pushbulletEmail, pushoverKey, slackRoom, slackWebhookUrl, tweetHandle, victorOpsApiKey, victorOpsCustomRoutingKey, victorOpsRoutingKeyType);
    Console.WriteLine(response);
}
catch(Exception ex)
{
    Console.WriteLine(ex.ToString());
}

args['pagerduty_autoresolve'] = false; // pagerduty_autoresolve
args['pagerduty_key'] = "samplePagerdutyKey"; // pagerduty_key
args['postback_url'] = "samplePostbackUrl"; // postback_url
args['pushbullet_email'] = "samplePushbulletEmail"; // pushbullet_email
args['pushover_key'] = "samplePushoverKey"; // pushover_key
args['slack_room'] = "sampleSlackRoom"; // slack_room
args['slack_webhook_url'] = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl"; // slack_webhook_url

args['victor_ops_api_key'] = "sampleVictorOpsApiKey"; // victor_ops_api_key
args['victor_ops_custom_routing_key'] = "sampleVictorOpsCustomRoutingKey"; // victor_ops_custom_routing_key

swagger.Web.pushNotificationAddHipChat(args, function(response) {
  /* success callback */
  console.log("Result of Web.pushNotificationAddHipChat");
  var result = response.obj;
  // print parsed result
  console.log(result);
  // print raw response in string
  console.log(response.data.toString());
}, function(response) {
  /* error callback */
  console.log('Error for Web.pushNotificationAddHipChat:', response.status); // status code
  console.log(response.data.toString()); // raw response
  //console.log(response.headers); // http headers for JS
  //console.log(response.headers.normalized); // http headers for Node.js
});

// initialize the API client with default base URL: https://uptime.com
$api_client = new UptimeApi\ApiClient();

$hipchatToken = "sampleHipchatToken";  // Hipchat Token
$alias = "sampleAlias";  // Alias
$hipchatRoom = "sampleHipchatRoom";  // Hipchat Room
$hipchatServer = "sampleHipchatServer";  // Hipchat Server
$pagerdutyAutoresolve = False;  // pagerduty_autoresolve
$pagerdutyKey = "samplePagerdutyKey";  // pagerduty_key
$postbackUrl = "samplePostbackUrl";  // postback_url
$pushbulletEmail = "samplePushbulletEmail";  // pushbullet_email
$pushoverKey = "samplePushoverKey";  // pushover_key
$slackRoom = "sampleSlackRoom";  // slack_room
$slackWebhookUrl = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl";  // slack_webhook_url
$tweetHandle = "sampleTweetHandle";  // tweet_handle
$victorOpsApiKey = "sampleVictorOpsApiKey";  // victor_ops_api_key
$victorOpsCustomRoutingKey = "sampleVictorOpsCustomRoutingKey";  // victor_ops_custom_routing_key
$victorOpsRoutingKeyType = False;  // victor_ops_routing_key_type

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->pushNotificationAddHipChat($hipchatToken, $alias, $hipchatRoom, $hipchatServer, $pagerdutyAutoresolve, $pagerdutyKey, $postbackUrl, $pushbulletEmail, $pushoverKey, $slackRoom, $slackWebhookUrl, $tweetHandle, $victorOpsApiKey, $victorOpsCustomRoutingKey, $victorOpsRoutingKeyType);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
}

    pprint(response)

except ApiException as e:

hipchat_token = "sample_hipchat_token"  # Hipchat Token

begin
  web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
  # return PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.push_notification_add_hip_chat(hipchat_token, :_alias => "sample_alias", :hipchat_room => "sample_hipchat_room", :hipchat_server => "sample_hipchat_server", :pagerduty_autoresolve => false, :pagerduty_key => "sample_pagerduty_key", :postback_url => "sample_postback_url", :pushbullet_email => "sample_pushbullet_email", :pushover_key => "sample_pushover_key", :slack_room => "sample_slack_room", :slack_webhook_url => "sample_slack_webhook_url", :tweet_handle => "sample_tweet_handle", :victor_ops_api_key => "sample_victor_ops_api_key", :victor_ops_custom_routing_key => "sample_victor_ops_custom_routing_key", :victor_ops_routing_key_type => false)
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
  puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"
end
The Scala SDK (REST API library) is still under development. Please contact api@uptime.com if you would like pilot the beta version of the SDK.

pushNotificationAddPagerDuty
Add a new Pager Duty Record

POST https://uptime.com/api/v1/alerting-push-notifications/add_pager_duty/

This endpoint helps you manage your Push Notification Add a new Pager Duty Record

    web_api = uptime_api.WebApi(apiclient)

    # return PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer (model)

$hipchatRoom = "sampleHipchatRoom";  // hipchat_room
$hipchatServer = "sampleHipchatServer";  // hipchat_server
$hipchatToken = "sampleHipchatToken";  // hipchat_token
$pagerdutyAutoresolve = False;  // pagerduty_autoresolve
$pagerdutyKey = "samplePagerdutyKey";  // pagerduty_key
$postbackUrl = "samplePostbackUrl";  // postback_url
$pushoverKey = "samplePushoverKey";  // pushover_key
$slackRoom = "sampleSlackRoom";  // slack_room
$slackWebhookUrl = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl";  // slack_webhook_url
$tweetHandle = "sampleTweetHandle";  // tweet_handle
$victorOpsApiKey = "sampleVictorOpsApiKey";  // victor_ops_api_key
$victorOpsCustomRoutingKey = "sampleVictorOpsCustomRoutingKey";  // victor_ops_custom_routing_key
$victorOpsRoutingKeyType = False;  // victor_ops_routing_key_type

    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->pushNotificationAddPushBullet($pushbulletEmail, $alias, $hipchatRoom, $hipchatServer, $hipchatToken, $pagerdutyAutoresolve, $pagerdutyKey, $postbackUrl, $pushoverKey, $slackRoom, $slackWebhookUrl, $tweetHandle, $victorOpsApiKey, $victorOpsCustomRoutingKey, $victorOpsRoutingKeyType);

// initialize the API client with default base URL: https://uptime.com
$api_client = new UptimeApi\ApiClient();

$victorOpsApiKey = "sampleVictorOpsApiKey";  // VictorOps API Key
$alias = "sampleAlias";  // Alias
$hipchatRoom = "sampleHipchatRoom";  // hipchat_room
$hipchatServer = "sampleHipchatServer";  // hipchat_server
$hipchatToken = "sampleHipchatToken";  // hipchat_token
$pagerdutyAutoresolve = False;  // pagerduty_autoresolve
$pagerdutyKey = "samplePagerdutyKey";  // pagerduty_key
$postbackUrl = "samplePostbackUrl";  // postback_url
$pushbulletEmail = "samplePushbulletEmail";  // pushbullet_email
$pushoverKey = "samplePushoverKey";  // pushover_key
$slackRoom = "sampleSlackRoom";  // slack_room
$slackWebhookUrl = "sampleSlackWebhookUrl";  // slack_webhook_url
$tweetHandle = "sampleTweetHandle";  // tweet_handle
$victorOpsCustomRoutingKey = "sampleVictorOpsCustomRoutingKey";  // VictorOps Routing Key
$victorOpsRoutingKeyType = False;  // victor_ops_routing_key_type

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->pushNotificationAddVictorOps($victorOpsApiKey, $alias, $hipchatRoom, $hipchatServer, $hipchatToken, $pagerdutyAutoresolve, $pagerdutyKey, $postbackUrl, $pushbulletEmail, $pushoverKey, $slackRoom, $slackWebhookUrl, $tweetHandle, $victorOpsCustomRoutingKey, $victorOpsRoutingKeyType);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
}

  web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
  # return PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.push_notification_add_victor_ops(victor_ops_api_key, :_alias => "sample_alias", :hipchat_room => "sample_hipchat_room", :hipchat_server => "sample_hipchat_server", :hipchat_token => "sample_hipchat_token", :pagerduty_autoresolve => false, :pagerduty_key => "sample_pagerduty_key", :postback_url => "sample_postback_url", :pushbullet_email => "sample_pushbullet_email", :pushover_key => "sample_pushover_key", :slack_room => "sample_slack_room", :slack_webhook_url => "sample_slack_webhook_url", :tweet_handle => "sample_tweet_handle", :victor_ops_custom_routing_key => "sample_victor_ops_custom_routing_key", :victor_ops_routing_key_type => false)
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
  puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"
end

pk = "sample_pk"  # pk

begin
  web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
  # return PushNotificationChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.push_notification_partial_update(pk, :_alias => "sample_alias", :hipchat_room => "sample_hipchat_room", :hipchat_server => "sample_hipchat_server", :hipchat_token => "sample_hipchat_token", :pagerduty_autoresolve => false, :pagerduty_key => "sample_pagerduty_key", :postback_url => "sample_postback_url", :pushbullet_email => "sample_pushbullet_email", :pushover_key => "sample_pushover_key", :slack_room => "sample_slack_room", :slack_webhook_url => "sample_slack_webhook_url", :tweet_handle => "sample_tweet_handle", :victor_ops_api_key => "sample_victor_ops_api_key", :victor_ops_custom_routing_key => "sample_victor_ops_custom_routing_key", :victor_ops_routing_key_type => false, :copyfro_mupdateandmakealloptional => "sample_copyfro_mupdateandmakealloptional")
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
  puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"
end

pushNotificationRetrieve
Get a Single Push Notification

GET https://uptime.com/api/v1/alerting-push-notifications/:pk/

This endpoint helps you manage your Push Notification Get a Single Push NotificationNote that the fields returned will vary based on the type of push notification that the record is. It will only show fields that are visible in the add_* POST methods and POST documentation.Whereas on the GET request listing all records, this shows all fields on the table exposed in the API and some fields might be blank even though the fields will be ignored for that type of check.


  • Parameter
  • Request
  • Response
  • Error Code

NameTypeLocationDescription
pkStringPart of URL

pk

This endpoint returns PushNotificationSerializer (model)


Error CodeMessage
400PARSE_ERROR
401NOT_AUTHORIZED
403PERMISSION_DENIED
404NOT_FOUND
500UNKNOWN

  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"

  /* success callback */
  console.log("Result of Web.userCreate");

  // print parsed result
  console.log(result);

  console.log(response.data.toString());

  //console.log(response.headers.normalized); // http headers for Node.js
});

// initialize the API client with default base URL: https://uptime.com
$api_client = new UptimeApi\ApiClient();

$firstName = "sampleFirstName";  // First Name
$lastName = "sampleLastName";  // Last Name
$email = "sampleEmail";  // Email Address
$password = "samplePassword";  // Password
$notifyUptimeReport = False;  // Notify Weekly Uptime Report

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return UserChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->userCreate($firstName, $lastName, $email, $password, $notifyUptimeReport);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
}

var args = {};
args['pk'] = "samplePk"; // pk
args['first_name'] = "sampleFirstName"; // First Name
args['last_name'] = "sampleLastName"; // Last Name
args['email'] = "sampleEmail"; // Email Address
args['password'] = "samplePassword"; // Password
args['notify_uptime_report'] = false; // Notify Weekly Uptime Report

swagger.Web.userPartialUpdate(args, function(response) {
  /* success callback */
  console.log("Result of Web.userPartialUpdate");
  var result = response.obj;
  // print parsed result
  console.log(result);
  // print raw response in string
  console.log(response.data.toString());
}, function(response) {
  /* error callback */
  console.log('Error for Web.userPartialUpdate:', response.status); // status code
  console.log(response.data.toString()); // raw response
  //console.log(response.headers); // http headers for JS
  //console.log(response.headers.normalized); // http headers for Node.js
});

Copy
// initialize the API client with default base URL: https://uptime.com
$api_client = new UptimeApi\ApiClient();

$pk = "samplePk";  // pk
$firstName = "sampleFirstName";  // First Name
$lastName = "sampleLastName";  // Last Name
$email = "sampleEmail";  // Email Address
$password = "samplePassword";  // Password
$notifyUptimeReport = False;  // Notify Weekly Uptime Report

try {
    $web_api = new UptimeApi\Api\WebAPI($api_client);
    // return UserChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    $response = $web_api->userPartialUpdate($pk, $firstName, $lastName, $email, $password, $notifyUptimeReport);
    print_r($response);
} catch (UptimeApi\ApiException $e) {
    echo 'Caught exception: ', $e->getMessage(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Header: ', $e->getResponseHeaders(), "\n";
    echo 'Resepone Body: ', $e->getResponseBody(), "\n";
}
Copy
pk = "sample_pk"  # pk

try:
    # (optional) initialize the API client with default base URL: http://petstore.swagger.io/v2
    api_client = uptime_api.ApiClient()
    web_api = uptime_api.WebApi(apiclient)

    # return UserChangeRecordSerializer (model)
    response = web_api.user_partial_update(pk, first_name="sample_first_name", last_name="sample_last_name", email="sample_email", password="sample_password", notify_uptime_report=False)    

    pprint(response)


    # asynchronous call
    # thread = web_api.user_partial_update(pk, first_name="sample_first_name", last_name="sample_last_name", email="sample_email", password="sample_password", notify_uptime_report=False, callback=callback_function)

except ApiException as e:
    print(e)
Copy
pk = "sample_pk"  # pk

begin
  web_api = UptimeApi::WebApi.new
  # return UserChangeRecordSerializer (model)
  response = web_api.user_partial_update(pk, :first_name => "sample_first_name", :last_name => "sample_last_name", :email => "sample_email", :password => "sample_password", :notify_uptime_report => false)
  p response
rescue UptimeApi::ApiError => e
  puts "Failed to call API! Error: #{e}"
  puts "Response code: #{e.code}"
  puts "Response headers: #{e.response_headers}"
  puts "Response body: #{e.response_body}"
end
